race.comment: BAVETTE (10) was a Kilmore winner on debut and then had no luck beaten less than 2L at Swan Hill first-up. Went well and has won a jumpout since with today's race rider John Allen aboard. Strips fitter and can bounce back. TATSU (4) missed a nose at Geelong from the front and then wound up strongly there beaten a nose over this distance. Jumps from a low draw and should prove tough to beat. BRULLEN (13) has threatened his last two with the near miss at Mornington the best of them. Ben Allen is reunited off that and he maps for the run of the race. VIVACISSIMO (6) resumes for the Hayes yard and has had three jumpouts. Comes off an easy 64 win at Pakenham over this distance and has to be given plenty of consideration.
